Osun Agency For Community and Social Development Project (CSDP) has assures of more interventions for the vulnerable members of the society, saying the organization is ahead of other states of the federation in assisting the vulnerable to be self reliant. The General Manager,  Osun CSDP,  Mrs Funmi Abokedeat made the disclosure in Osogbo while presenting the score card of the agency at the end of a two-day training programme for selected Journalists on CSDP interventions and language of operation. According to her, only five per cent contribution is required as counterpart funding for the vulnerable groups unlike community oriented project that requires 10 per cent contributions by communities. She explained that no fewer than one million, two hundred and sixty-six thousand people in four hundred and nineteen poor communities in the state have benefited from the interventions of the agency. Abokede said the interventions of the agency cut across critical sectors like Road, Electricity, Health, Education, Water, Environmental and Sanitation, and Social supports for the vulnerable in the state. Themed, “Empowerment of Poor Communities Through Community and Social Development Project,’’ Abokede said thousands of lives have been transformed through the laudable and life-changing programmes of the agency. She said, the agency, which started its operations in 2009 is using Community Driven Development approach in its interventions, adding that the system has proved very productive, just as she said  the agency has disbursed N3.7bn naira sourced from the World Bank (N2.9bn) and the state government of Osun (N813m). Abokede thanked the governor of the state, Mr Gboyega Oyetola for his support to the agency despite paucity of funds. She in the same vein appreciated the World Bank for their trust and support, promising to ensure further effective utilization of the funds. 